The first two limbs of ashtanga yoga (yamas and niyamas, Hinduism&#8217;s ten commandments) are the most important. But it is very difficult to do those without the other six limbs. The other six are for purifying the mind, or samskaras. <span class=date>12/12/76</span>
The right way is to do austerities of your own. In ashtanga yoga, the first four limbs are all austerities. <span class=date>12/12/76</span>
